### 1) Match request — create exchange + session (use requestId 1 first; if 400, use 1b)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/transactions/match-request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "offerId": 4,
  "requestId": 1,
  "conversationId": 3,
  "scheduledStart": "2025-03-15 10:00:00",
  "scheduledEnd": "2025-03-15 11:00:00",
  "venue": "ITU Lab 1"
}

### 1b) Match request — alternative (when requestId 1 is already matched)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/transactions/match-request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "offerId": 7,
  "requestId": 3,
  "conversationId": 3,
  "scheduledStart": "2025-03-15 10:00:00",
  "scheduledEnd": "2025-03-15 11:00:00",
  "venue": "ITU Lab 1"
}

### 2) Paid exchange — record payment for exchange 111
POST http://localhost:5000/api/v1/transactions/paid-exchange
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "exchangeId": 111,
  "price": 750,
  "currency": "PKR",
  "paymentMethod": "JazCash"
}
